mage/width=384,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20231202_WBC544.png">他们的图表</a>显示我们的电动汽车销售仍在上升！ CNBC引用了有关经销商销售其电动汽车库存需要多长时间的数据，但是鉴于销售的增加，这只是经销商过于乐观和订购太多的标志。 Money.com文章将电动汽车销售与预期进行了比较，而不是实际销售的前一年。</p><p>当您查看实际数据时，很明显，到目前为止，实际上还没有放缓。在2023年，美国人已经购买了超过200,000辆电动汽车。 </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F72bb6ce6-3dec-4244-a0c3-cd15e025a7c5_900x565.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F72bb6ce6-3dec-4244-a0c3-cd15e025a7c5_900x565.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F72bb6ce6-3dec-4244-a0c3-cd15e025a7c5_900x565.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F72bb6ce6-3dec-4244-a0c3-cd15e025a7c5_900x565.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F72bb6ce6-3dec-4244-a0c3-cd15e025a7c5_900x565.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F72bb6ce6-3dec-4244-a0c3-cd15e025a7c5_900x565.jpeg" width="900" height="565" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/72bb6ce6-3dec-4244-a0c3-cd15e025a7c5_900x565.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:565,&quot;width&quot;:900,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:93836,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F72bb6ce6-3dec-4244-a0c3-cd15e025a7c5_900x565.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F72bb6ce6-3dec-4244-a0c3-cd15e025a7c5_900x565.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F72bb6ce6-3dec-4244-a0c3-cd15e025a7c5_900x565.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F72bb6ce6-3dec-4244-a0c3-cd15e025a7c5_900x565.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源：Corey Cantor</figcaption></figure></div><p></p><p>很抱歉，仅仅因为电动汽车的销售比预期的，或者比欧洲和中国少，这并不意味着电动汽车的过渡已经“停滞不前”。这只是意味着我们需要<em>进一步</em>加速过渡。是的，值得担心缺乏充电站，以及一些美国人尚未确信电动汽车是未来的事实。但是关于EV革命“停滞”的叙述似乎是一个假趋势。</p><h4> 4.美国孩子受过良好的教育，除了数学</h4><p>我<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/refusing-to-teach-kids-math-will">经常抱怨</a>美国数学焦虑在整个文化中普遍存在，我们倾向于<a href="https://twitter.com/cremieuxrecueil/status/1730646739407851962">低调主题</a>。但这就是说，我们的教育系统的总体表现实际上并不那么可怕。 <a href="https://www.axios.com/2023/12/05/us-students-pisa-global-assessment">PISA的结果已经消失</a>，尽管美国的表现比以前更糟 - 部分是由于大流行学习损失，但我们仍然领先于中位数。</p><p>尤其是，如果您通过种族打破我们的PISA结果，您会发现，尽管我们的数学教育系统非常<em>不平等</em>，但它并不像您想象的那样可怕。黑人的孩子的<a href="https://twitter.com/cremieuxrecueil/status/1732087511327908128">表现优于</a>罗马尼亚人，希腊和保加利亚的孩子，而西班牙裔美国人的表现要比斯洛伐克，冰岛和塞尔维亚孩子更好： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6b0c7b95-ad1e-4649-b7bd-f59c5c912534_1228x983.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6b0c7b95-ad1e-4649-b7bd-f59c5c912534_1228x983.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6b0c7b95-ad1e-4649-b7bd-f59c5c912534_1228x983.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6b0c7b95-ad1e-4649-b7bd-f59c5c912534_1228x983.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6b0c7b95-ad1e-4649-b7bd-f59c5c912534_1228x983.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-