stancil/status/1730756792290836950">反驳</a>说，由于通货膨胀已经下降，而且从来没有像1970年代那样严重 - 对经济的愤怒只是“共鸣”。</p><p>基本上，拜登支持者是正确的。现在，美国的经济确实是出色的。<a href="https://twitter.com/jasonfurman/status/1730229041049874546">通货膨胀看起来像是节拍</a>，每个人都有工作，收入和财富正在上升，依此类推。但是，另一方面，我不能命令人们只是不再对在2021  -  22年降低他们的购买力的通货膨胀感到生气。人们关心他们关心的东西。</p><p>不过，与此同时，我认为关于经济的负面叙述可能会在普通民众中占据，并扭曲人们对实际发生的事情的理解。例如，《金融时报》的约翰·伯恩·穆尔多奇（John Burn-Murdoch）<a href="https://t.co/FKpRNQkBVf">最近发现</a>，消费者的情绪仔细跟踪了其他国家的真实经济指标，但自2020年以来在美国差异： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc5a18c0e-1cfb-4408-a4b0-f2986a2ad945_656x1200.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc5a18c0e-1cfb-4408-a4b0-f2986a2ad945_656x1200.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc5a18c0e-1cfb-4408-a4b0-f2986a2ad945_656x1200.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc5a18c0e-1cfb-4408-a4b0-f2986a2ad945_656x1200.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc5a18c0e-1cfb-4408-a4b0-f2986a2ad945_656x1200.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc5a18c0e-1cfb-4408-a4b0-f2986a2ad945_656x1200.