height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p>但是，再次观察负面叙述如何使人们看到<em>任何</em>数据是不良经济的标志。如果通货膨胀率低，数百万美元失业，就像2009年的情况一样，您是否认为“ Deusexmoniker”会认为这是人们足够富有的人不工作，因为食品和天然气和租金负担得起？我非常怀疑。</p><p>接下来，该男子引用了<a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-09-06/us-labor-department-sees-much-slower-job-growth-through-2032?sref=R8NfLgwS">彭博社的一篇文章</a>，声称在接下来的十年中，就业前景很沮丧： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa4c94376-2f91-437f-813e-042591b5aa4e_823x824.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa4c94376-2f91-437f-813e-042591b5aa4e_823x824.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa4c94376-2f91-437f-813e-042591b5aa4e_823x824.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa4c94376-2f91-437f-813e-042591b5aa4e_823x824.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa4c94376-2f91-437f-813e-042591b5aa4e_823x824.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa4c94376-2f91-437f-813e-042591b5aa4e_823x824.jpeg" width="618" height="618.7509113001215" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/a4c94376-2f91-437f-813e-042591b5aa4e_823x824.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:824,&quot;width&quot;:823,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:618,&quot;bytes&quot;:122837,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa4c94376-2f91-437f-813e-042591b5aa4e_823x824.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa4c94376-2f91-437f-813e-042591b5aa4e_823x824.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa4c94376-2f91-437f-813e-042591b5aa4e_823x824.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa4c94376-2f91-437f-813e-042591b5aa4e_823x824.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p>但实际上，彭博文章并没有将此预测描述为经济弱点的标志。 <a href="https://www.bls.gov/news.release/ecopro.nr0.htm">BLS也没有报告</a>彭博文章正在报告。实际上，投影缓慢的工作增长是两件事的函数：</p><ol><li><p>经济已经达到了充分就业的事实，因此那里没有更多的增加空间，而且</p></li><li><p>美国人口正在变老，很多人都在退休。</p></li></ol><p>在这里，让我们的BLS报告自己说话：</p><blockquote><p>预计人口的预计增长速度有望限制预测期内平民劳动力的增长……这意味着预计的年增长率为0.4％，比2012  -  22年十年中表现出的0.6％的年增长率慢。</p><p>预计总就业总额将从2022年的1.645亿每年增长0.3％，增长到2032年的1.611亿。这种预计增长远远低于2012  -  22年十年中的1.2％的年度就业增长，这是恢复的强劲增长。 2007-09大萧条和2020年Covid-19衰退。</p></blockquote><p>再一次，关于经济的负面叙述导致“去耐药者”解释经济实力的迹象 - 充分就业，即增加工作的空间不足 - 作为经济弱点的证明。</p><p>无论如何，整个线程中的错误仍在继续。他大大夸大了美国<a href="https://twitter.com/Noahpinion/status/1730652739737448464">负担不起住房的</a>工人的数量以及报告正在遭受<a href="https://twitter.com/Noahpinion/status/1730653931939000638">粮食不安全感</a>的人数。他认为，预计的净创造净工作不足以跟上人口增长，而<a href="https://twitter.com/Noahpinion/status/1730718812461539518">忽略了</a>大量也是预测的退休。他声称，当实际上<a href="https://twitter.com/Noahpinion/status/1730719712852717712">犯罪的情况</a>下，每个人都落后于他们的信用卡和汽车贷款。等等。在任何情况下，他对经济的负面叙述都推动了他对数字的误解。</p><p>正如我所说，我在这里的目的不是反驳一个随机的Twitter家伙。我的目的是指出，经济事实对叙事具有有限的权力，因为叙事可以使我们对事实的解释进行色彩，或者诱使我们相信不正确的事情。当《金融时报》对美国公众有关实际工资，通货膨胀，财富和中位数收入进行调查时，他们发现负面信念比正确的答案更为普遍。 </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F046b58dc-db24-4bb6-a6ae-8b84f209e45e_471x744.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F046b58dc-db24-4bb6-a6ae-8b84f209e45e_471x744.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F046b58dc-db24-4bb6-a6ae-8b84f209e45e_471x744.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F046b58dc-db24-4bb6-a6ae-8b84f209e45e_471x744.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F046b58dc-db24-4bb6-a6ae-8b84f209e45e_471x744.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F046b58dc-db24-4bb6-a6ae-8b84f209e45e_471x744.jpeg" width="471" height="744" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/046b58dc-db24-4bb6-a6ae-8b84f209e45e_471x744.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:744,&quot;width&quot;:471,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:117053,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F046b58dc-db24-4bb6-a6ae-8b84f209e45e_471x744.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F046b58dc-db24-4bb6-a6ae-8b84f209e45e_471x744.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F046b58dc-db24-4bb6-a6ae-8b84f209e45e_471x744.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F046b58dc-db24-4bb6-a6ae-8b84f209e45e_471x744.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源：John Burn-Murdoch通过<a href="https://twitter.com/analisapackham/status/1730954160130912328">Analisa Packham</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>如果您想对通货膨胀，工资，财富，收入等发生的事情感到沮丧，那么您就有一个完美的沮丧权。 But at least <em>you should know what&#39;s actually happening</em> . But lots of people simply don&#39;t know.</p><p> Some will be quick to interpret mistakes about the national economic situation as stemming from <em>personal lived experience</em> — the idea being that people care about their own financial situation much more than some abstract national statistics. But <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2022/07/15/business/economy/inflation-economy-polling.html">when you poll people</a> about their personal economic situation, they&#39;re <em>much more positive</em> than they are about the national economy as a whole. Here&#39;s <a href="https://www.axios.com/2023/08/18/americans-economy-bad-personal-finances-good">Axios back in August</a> :</p><blockquote><p> A majority of Americans think the economy is in bad shape, but at the same time say their own finances are good, finds a new poll out from Quinnipiac University this week…In the telephone survey of 1,818 adults Aug. 10-14,<strong> </strong>71% of Americans described the economy as either not so good or poor. And 51% said it&#39;s getting worse…But <strong>60% said their financial situation is good or excellent</strong> …&quot;Can you be generally happy with your personal financial position and still think the economy is going in the tank? For a broad section of Americans, apparently so,&quot; Quinnipiac University polling analyst Tim Malloy said in a <a href="https://poll.qu.edu/images/polling/us/us08162023_usos65.pdf">press release</a> . （强调我的）</p></blockquote><p> In other words, something is convincing a lot of Americans that the national economy is a lot worse than their own lived experience would suggest — and causing them to get the facts wrong in the process. That something is what commentators, for lack of a better word, are calling “vibes”.</p><p> Where do these negative narratives come from? <a href="https://www.offmessage.net/p/social-media-economic-despair">Brian Beutler</a> and <a href="https://www.slowboring.com/p/the-biggest-problem-in-media-is-the">Matt Yglesias</a> both blame negativity bias — the fact that scary narratives get more attention than happy ones — for filling our screens with portents of doom. But of course negativity bias has always existed; it seems to me that this explanation only works if either A) people are consuming more news than before, and/or B) the replacement of traditional media with social media has exacerbated negativity bias. And since the weird break between economic fundamentals and consumer confidence appears to exist only in America, this explanation would require media&#39;s negativity bias to be much less powerful in Europe.</p><p> Which leads me to suspect that although negativity bias is certainly a factor, something else is going on here. The fact that the problem is US-specific suggests that either a special feature of American society and politics is at work here, or the American media and social media landscape differs from Europe&#39;s in key ways. Since Europeans have Twitter and Facebook and TikTok too, and their newspapers and TV news shows aren&#39;t <em>that</em> different from ours, I suspect US social and political factors as the cause of the peculiar presence of negative narratives.</p><p> In any case, the question is how we commentators can fight the dominance of the vibes — not because we want to convince everyone that the economy is great, but because people need facts if they&#39;re going to know whether the economy is good or bad 。 But I&#39;m afraid that&#39;s one question I don&#39;t have a good answer to. Perhaps we should just keep relentlessly reminding everyone of the facts, while waiting for the populace to finally realize that economic fundamentals have improved.</p><p> <strong>Update</strong> : Here&#39;s a poll of young Americans that reinforces the notion that negative narratives about the national economy are causing people to think the rest of the country is doing worse than they are: </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff6f10a46-877a-4529-baf4-ec31271f3259_889x778.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff6f10a46-877a-4529-baf4-ec31271f3259_889x778.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff6f10a46-877a-4529-baf4-ec31271f3259_889x778.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsu